column5: Here are the other photos.  I figured out the picture thing.       YES!!!  I am such an Idiot!!!
No, Fished lake X on Friday.
Yep, I recognize those picture. Seen them before.
OMG!!!  It's the dreaded Albino Catfish in a snow storm!!!
Hey Bud...I can't see the pics. I guess you know that you need to use both hands to post pics?
In my mind's eye those are some real nice fish!
Wow, I am such a block head, enjoy the pics.
I only see 3 pictures not 4  Nice pics though!  G
Nice pics !!!!...hey man i know where that lake is...its lake Z    , not lake X...  ..aha,now we know where it is,ill be there next weekend and catch some of those too !!!!....cheers
Thats not lake Y thats the Lower Grand River Dunnville..  It was wonderful meeting you guys yesterday!  Look forward to seeing you again soon!  Cheers and have a great week!  Jen

Sorry Jen  ,  We don't like sharing our fishing spots, especially when there as good as the river in front of your place.  Had we known we would have saved our selves a trip to Dog Lake last year.  Anyways you guys have a great place and we will be back again soon(When I get back on the 23 of Feb)

I don't mind sharing my fishing spots, it just means more people will have the opportunity to enjoy great moments.  Thank you for the compliment on our place.  Both Steve (fishmaster) and I are enjoying it greatly... a little piece of paradise in an otherwise hectic world.  Look forward to seeing you again!  Cheers,  Jen  p.s.  I got my first walleye through the ice today... I think you will know exactly where that was.

Very Cool, The river channel out from that little bay was the ticket for us.  Steve said he wanted to try figuring out the night bite on the river, when i get back home I am going to try to do exactly that.  We marked and caught more fish in three hours there then we have at many places further up North.  Congrats and my wife and I will see you in a couple of weeks.
